Created by PLY version 3.11 (http://www.dabeaz.com/ply)

Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> program
Rule 1     program -> statements
Rule 2     statements -> statements statement
Rule 3     statements -> statement
Rule 4     expression -> expression PLUS expression
Rule 5     expression -> expression MINUS expression
Rule 6     expression -> expression TIMES expression
Rule 7     expression -> expression DIVIDE expression
Rule 8     expression -> NUMBER
Rule 9     expression -> ID
Rule 10    condition -> expression GREATER expression
Rule 11    condition -> expression LESS expression
Rule 12    condition -> expression EQUAL_EQUAL expression
Rule 13    condition -> expression GREATER_EQUAL expression
Rule 14    condition -> expression LESS_EQUAL expression
Rule 15    condition -> expression NOT_EQUAL expression
Rule 16    statement -> PRINT STRING
Rule 17    statement -> PRINT ID
Rule 18    statement -> LET ID EQUALS expression
Rule 19    statement -> LET ID EQUALS STRING
Rule 20    statement -> IF condition statements END
Rule 21    statement -> IF condition statements ELSE statements END
Rule 22    statement -> IF condition statements ELIF condition statements END
Rule 23    statement -> IF condition statements ELIF condition statements ELSE statements END
Rule 24    statement -> FOR ID EQUALS expression TO expression statements END
Rule 25    statement -> WHILE condition statements END

Terminals, with rules where they appear

DIVIDE               : 7
ELIF                 : 22 23
ELSE                 : 21 23
END                  : 20 21 22 23 24 25
EQUALS               : 18 19 24
EQUAL_EQUAL          : 12
FOR                  : 24
GREATER              : 10
GREATER_EQUAL        : 13
ID                   : 9 17 18 19 24
IF                   : 20 21 22 23
LESS                 : 11
LESS_EQUAL           : 14
LET                  : 18 19
MINUS                : 5
NOT_EQUAL            : 15
NUMBER               : 8
PLUS                 : 4
PRINT                : 16 17
STRING               : 16 19
TIMES                : 6
TO                   : 24
WHILE                : 25
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

condition            : 20 21 22 22 23 23 25
expression           : 4 4 5 5 6 6 7 7 10 10 11 11 12 12 13 13 14 14 15 15 18 24 24
program              : 0
statement            : 2 3
statements           : 1 2 20 21 21 22 22 23 23 23 24 25

